What is AI? ML? DL? NN?

Define AI, ML, DL, NN

AI is most often just a term for business people to describe Machine Learning (ML), which is a set of algorithms that allow statistical/mathematical models to learn and thus predict with greater accuracy than standard statistical models. That improved accuracy often comes at the expense of model interpretability or inference. In general, ML algorithms arent new, however, computing resource improvements and data size increases have enabled more prolific use of ML in the past five years.

Define Data Science

Data Science is the confluence of statistical design, computer science, machine learning modeling, and the domain knowledge of researchers/experts. Data science teams often include a blend of data engineers, technical business analysts and project managers, statisticians, business intelligence (BI) developers, front-end and/or back-end developers (DevOps), and machine learning researchers. Most data scientists are either generalist data scientists, data engineers, or machine learning researchers, though this distinction is only a year or two old. I consider myself a generalist.

Governance

AI Ethics in Product Development

Must maintain ethics in

  • Content / Product
  • Process

Ethics are defined as:

  • As beneficial as possible
  • Respect human agency
  • Allow human development
  • Ensure social justice

AI Ethics Concerns in Dentistry

Model Governance Considerations

Coming Opportunities & Cool Stuff

AI for Creativity

Human visual system / object recognition shows that we see detail in the middle but not on the periphery. See if I can find the Adobe example Zoya ? Eye tracking is expensive and difficult. However, Adobe is building a real-time reflow design based on deep learning results. Meaning you change A/B testing to real-time design optimization, or attention mapping.
